%N A344649 Triangle read by rows where T(n,k) is the number of strict integer partitions of 2*n with reverse-alternating sum 2*k.
%C A344649 The reverse-alternating sum of a partition (y_1,...,y_k) is Sum_i (-1)^(k-i) y_i. This is equal to (-1)^(m-1) times the number of odd parts in the conjugate partition, where m is the number of parts. So T(n,k) is the number of strict integer partitions of 2n into an odd number of parts whose conjugate has exactly 2k odd parts.
%C A344649 Also the number of reversed strict integer partitions of 2n with alternating sum 2k.
%C A344649 Also the number of partitions of n+2*k^2 into 2*k distinct parts containing the part 2*k, except when n = k = 0. - _Seiichi Manyama_, May 16 2026
%H A344649 Seiichi Manyama, <a href="/A344649/b344649.txt">Rows n = 0..139, flattened</a>
%F A344649 From _Seiichi Manyama_, May 16 2026: (Start)
%F A344649 G.f. of column k: Sum_{i=1..2*k} q^(i*(i-1)+k) * q_binomial(2*k-1,i-1) / Product_{j=1..i-1} (1-q^j) for k > 0.
%F A344649 G.f. of column k: Sum_{i=1..2*k} (-1)^(i-1) * q^(i*(i-1)/2+k) / Product_{j=1..2*k-i} (1-q^j) for k > 0. (End)
